<subSubSection id="C368652E935E8E03F2AAFC5CFC8EFB9F" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935E8E03F2AAFC5CFC8EFB9F" blockId="7.[151,1437,974,1181]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF8935E8E03F2AAFC5CFC8AFB9F" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147315" collectorName="D. Eschscholtz" location="The" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kamchatka" typeStatus="lectotype">
<location id="8EAD607E935E8E03F2AAFC5CFF12FC23" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DB87B3935E8E03F2AAFC14FBADFB57:8EAD607E935E8E03F2AAFC5CFF12FC23" box="[151,195,974,1000]" name="The" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">The</location>
specimen here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935E8E03F029FC5CFDAAFC23" box="[532,635,974,1000]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a male bearing the labels: “male symbol”, “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935E8E03F6B3FC5CFB3BFC23" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[1166,1258,974,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solitaris">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F6B3FC5CFB3BFC23" box="[1166,1258,974,1000]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">solitaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. Eschscholtz in 
<collectingRegion id="49B6F847935E8E03F289FC60FE97FBC7" box="[180,326,1010,1036]" country="Russia" name="Kamchatka" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Kamtschatka</collectingRegion>
<collectorName id="26875373935E8E03F373FC61FDD1FBC7" box="[334,512,1010,1037]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">D. Eschscholtz.</collectorName>
” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935E8E03F077FC60FD6CFBC7" box="[586,701,1010,1036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935E8E03F0DEFC60FB9CFBC7" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[739,1101,1010,1036]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solitaris">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F0DEFC60FC61FBC7" box="[739,944,1010,1036]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Harpalus solitaris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F18AFC60FB9CFBC7" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[951,1101,1010,1036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
design. by 
<collectorName id="26875373935E8E03F6F2FC61FA94FBC7" box="[1231,1349,1010,1037]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”. These labels thus match the original description: 
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935E8E03F053FB84FAB2FBFB" box="[622,1379,1046,1073]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">
Il se trouve au 
<collectingRegion id="49B6F847935E8E03F12FFB84FC76FBFB" box="[786,935,1046,1072]" country="Russia" name="Kamchatka" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Kamtschatka</collectingRegion>
, et il m’a été envoyé par 
<collectorName id="26875373935E8E03F686FB85FAB2FBFB" box="[1211,1379,1046,1072]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">M. Eschscholtz</collectorName>
</emphasis>
. The other specimen in Dejean’s collection becomes a 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935E8E03F0FDFBA8FC8AFB9F" box="[704,859,1082,1108]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">paralectotype</typeStatus>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E935E8E03F2FAFBCCFBADFB57" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935E8E03F2FAFBCCFBADFB57" blockId="7.[151,1437,974,1181]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">
The species is found in most countries of Europe and also across Siberia reaching the Pacific Ocean, northern 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935E8E03F2AAFB10FF0CFB57" box="[151,221,1154,1180]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">China</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935E8E03F373FB11FE5FFB56" box="[334,398,1155,1181]" name="Japan" pageId="7" pageNumber="491">Japan</collectingCountry>
and northern parts of North America (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F106FB10FC04FB57" author="Kataev, B. M." box="[827,981,1154,1180]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" pagination="721 - 736" refId="ref11345" refString="Kataev, B. M. (2002) Taxonomic, faunistic and nomenclatural notes on certain Palaearctic and Oriental Harpalini (Coleoptera, Carabidae). Linzer Biologische Beitrage, 34, 721 - 736." type="journal article" year="2002">Kataev, 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935E8E03F1E2FB11FBA1FB57" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[991,1136,1154,1181]" pageId="7" pageNumber="491" pagination="344 - 386" refId="ref12516" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2004) Harpalina. In: Freude, H., Harde, K. W., Lohse, G. A. &amp; Klausnitzer, B. (Eds.), Die Kafer Mitteleuropas. Bd. 2 Adephaga 1: Carabidae (Laufkafer). Spektrum-Verlag, Heidelberg / Berlin, pp. 344 - 386." type="book chapter" year="2004">Wrase, 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
